properties.areaDesc: South Laramie Range Foothills; South Laramie Range
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 30 at 12:41PM MST until January 30 at 6:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...Accumulating snow this afternoon over the Interstate 80 Summit
and South Laramie Range Foothills...

* WHAT...Snow. Snow accumulations of up to 3 inches. Winds gusting
as high as 45 mph.

* WHERE...South Laramie Range and Foothills including the Interstate
80 Summit.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM MST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Patchy blowing snow
could significantly reduce visibility. The hazardous conditions
could impact the evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM MST THIS EVENING
